  "texts": [
    "Wang et al.",
    "proposed Fed-CAMS in [182], which combines the Federated AMSGrad adaptive gradient method with Max Stabilization and uses error feedback compression to reduce communication costs.",
    "GossipFL [183] uses the sparsified model to reduce communication and gossip matrix for efficient utilization of the bandwidth resources.",
    "presented the QSFL algorithm in [184], which samples high-qualification clients for model updates and compresses each update to a single segment.",
    "Zhu et al. [185] addressed system heterogeneity and communication efficiency in unstable connections with the Fed-ResCuE algorithm, focusing on the self-distillation of prunable neural networks on clients."
